LAGOS  – The operator of the Otakikpo Marginal Field in OML-11, Green Energy International Ltd (GEIL) said it is set to commission the 12MMSCFD modular LPG extraction plant and 6MW power generating plants at the field in the second quarter of 2022. The company explained that the project is aimed at eliminating gas flaring, industrialising the host community by using the gas to generate energy to the benefit both host community and the country at large. Johnson Akinyemi, the Projects General Manager, said when completed, the project will supply daily about 60-metric-tonnes of LPG (cooking gas) to the domestic market. SEPCOL’s Oil Field Fire Extinguished, Evacuation Operation… Petroleum Retailers Explain Crusade Against Illegal Refiners The plant, he said, works on a Hybrid System and consist of four major processes of compression, dehydration, refrigeration, and hydrocarbon separation. Professor Anthony Adegbulugbe, the Chairman of the company, said contrary to extant and industry belief, Green Energy International Limited has been able to achieve these fascinating results without jeopardising traditional and critical key financial key performance indicators that organizations use to track, measure, and analyze the financial health of organizations. He added: “GEIL has always emphasized the importance of delivering reliable and affordable energy to the world without jeopardizing environmental and social excellence. “It is a commitment to this sustainable culture that propelled the Company to prioritize, plan and implement the development of associated gas reserves in parallel with the oil reserves; a very atypical strategy that clearly separates us from our peers in the industry. He expressed satisfaction with the progress that the company has made in its efforts to ensuring the green-house effect is eliminated completely in GEIL operations. In his words, POLL “We will continue to strive to position our Company as one of the elite companies to deliver the energy the world deserves through a powerful combination of capital efficiency, low costs and sustainable development. “The company’s undisputable metrics has demonstrated that its unique underlying framework for success has delivered financial sustainability to its stakeholders that are competitive not only with our direct E&P peers, but the broader market. In terms of sustainable development, it is safe to admit that Green Energy International Limited (GEIL) is surely ahead of the pack. It is a Company that has have intentionally chosen the path least travelled and have emerged as an undisputed leader amongst our peers.” He concluded. HSE GM, Mr. Chuks Igbokwe the Company’s Chairman, while Commenting on the safety performance, said GEIL has developed and implemented its own program “Life-Saving Actions and Barrier Checks” in all its area of operations. “These Life-Saving Actions are meant to draw attention to activities that could most likely to lead to a fatality and implementing the critical, life-saving actions over which an individual has control. “This approach is in line with the Company’s established and enduring core beliefs at GEIL, that safety is not the absence of incidents, but rather it is the presence of defenses.” Igbokwe added. Senate Promises Support For Frontier Exploration Deregulation: Economist Advises FG Not To Adjust Petroleum Act The company said the project would be the first to be installed in the country and reiterated its intention to showcase the success of the project to other industry players and the government as one of its contributions to eliminating associated gas flares in Nigerian oil fields.